- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a likely category as the paper deals with a fundamental problem in parameterized complexity theory and proposes a new algorithm for it.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is also a likely category as the paper discusses the complexity of the hitting set problem and proposes a new algorithm that improves upon existing ones.
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is a possible category as the paper deals with hypergraphs and introduces a new notion of hypergraph sunflowers.
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is a possible category as the hitting set problem is a well-studied problem in game theory and the paper proposes a new algorithm for it.
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is a possible category as the paper discusses the parallelization of the hitting set kernel algorithm and proposes a new parallel algorithm for it.
